==English==
===Intransitive verb phrase===
'''to strike out''', (past '''struck out''')

# to yield nothing
#: ''Dave '''struck out''' with the blonde.''
#{{baseball}} to be retired after three strikes
#: ''He '''struck out''' on a nasty slider.''

===Transitive verb phrase===
'''to strike out''', (past '''struck out''')

#{{baseball}} to retire a batter after three strikes
#: ''He '''struck out''' Jones with a nasty slider.''



